""
"Final score: 3.96"
"Awesome that NG finally came out with a pumpkin beer, and did a great job on it.  This beer is a beautiful cloudy orangish brown (it is a part-wheat beer and brewed using weisen yeast, so it is supposed to be cloudy).  nifty lacing.  The spices are there, heaviest on the nutmeg, but not at all overwhelming.  the style is almost perfect for a pumpkin beer, which imho does not benefit from a crisp lager treatment.  not very sweet, but this aids in the drinkability department.  I sure as hell hope they bring this back in future years--I'll certainly be enjoying it while it lasts this season!"
