"O - New Glarus' first pumpkin beer; long has it been anticipated! And, instead of going the normal route, they've carved out a brand new path in the world of pumpkin beers - a pumpkin weiss! (I've yet to experience one - even the pumpkin beer connoisseur I am.) Pumpkin Pie Lust's aroma is immediately different and hard to pinpoint with both pie spices and weiss yeast being used in conjunction but, this beer has a great malt profile that carries through the flavor into the soft feel making it a unique and quite drinkable pumpkin beer from one of my favorite breweries!"
"This pours a murky brown color with a foamy light brown head. The aroma is rich with pumpkin and spices. The flavor is smooth and rich with pumpkin and spice flavors. Delicious and well-made."
